ude toward women formed the basis for virtually all later attempts at their organization. United Apart transforms conventional wisdom on the rise of the AFL by showing how its member unions developed their central beliefs about female workers and how those beliefs affected male workers as well.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aLabor unionszUnited StatesxHistory. 0aSexismzUnited StatesxHistory. 0aStrikes and lockoutszUnited StatesxHistory. 0aWomen labor union memberszUnited StatesxHistory. 4aGender Studies. 4aLabor History.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013z978311053615740uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150172707840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501727078423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501727078/original  a978-3-11-053615-7  Cornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles